Definition: a minimum credit balance that a bank may require a borrower to keep on deposit as a condition for granting a loan
Example: a common requirement for establishing a line of credit at a bank; the compensating balance increases the effective interest rate to the bank since the net amount loaned is reduced but the interest paid is unchanged
Synonyms: offsetting_balance, balance, a, minimum, credit, that, bank, may, require, borrower, to, keep, on, deposit, as, condition, for, granting, loan, common, requirement, establishing, line, of, at, the, compensating, increases, effective, interest, rate, since, net, amount, loaned, is, reduced, but, paid, unchanged
Category: noun.possession
